
[1]irrecoverably

   IRRECOV'ERABLY, adv. Beyond recovery; beyond the possibility of being
   regained, repaired or remedied. Happiness may be irrecoverably lost.

   1. Beyond the possibility of being reclaimed. A profligate may be
   irrecoverably abandoned to vice.

   A profligate may be irrecoverably abandoned to vice.
